 Job Title:  VP, Scientific Marketing 
 
 Position Summary:
 The Vice President, Scientific Marketing, through collaboration with all key functions, will lead the scientific marketing team, based out of Phoenix, AZ, and drive the global commercial go to market strategy and implementation for the Caris molecular science and artificial intelligence product portfolio. 
 This position is responsible for developing the overall product/portfolio vision, strategy and implementation plan including life cycle management, resource optimization and product launch strategy in the US and potential global markets. This individual will also be responsible for representing the commercial organization and providing cross-functional leadership by actively partnering with Clinical Development, Research, Medical Affairs, Finance, Market Access, Legal/Regulatory, Corporate Communications and Business Development teams, to develop and implement an integrated global product strategy and coordinated execution. 
 This individual will be an active member of Carisâ€™s senior marketing and strategy leadership team to shape and inform Carisâ€™s go to market commercial and business strategy. This individual will have a strong grasp of the precision medicine landscape, a high scientific and business acumen and will responsible for identifying and proactively resolving product issues or needs related to commercial circumstance and market demands. 
 
 Job Responsibilities: 
 Build a diverse multifunctional life cycle and early commercial team providing cross-functional partnership across research, development, market access and commercial/marketing activities 
 Develop a unified product portfolio vision and strategy based on target product profiles, key claims and market insights for the portfolio
 Mobilize the organization to maximize the value of the Caris MI/AI portfolio over the entire lifecycle by developing and implementing strategic life cycle, product development and launch plans for each product that meet patient and customer needs 
 Conduct targeted market and competitive research in collaboration with the team to develop and establish product positioning, messaging, revenue forecast and NPV valuations, as well as support regulatory, pricing and reimbursement strategic approaches 
 Lead forecasting and budgeting efforts to optimize P&L across the portfolio and programs 
 Develop a deep understanding of all key stakeholders and build meaningful relationships with key internal and external partners, including thought leaders, regional/national partners, speakers, patient advocacy groups, professional societies and agencies to prepare for a successful launch and subsequent growth 
 Partner across functions to architect the optimal commercial strategy, launch plan, resources and subsequent growth plan for Caris, and contribute to post-launch commercial success. 
 Collaborate with BD and other executive members to optimize portfolio assets and evaluate Carisâ€™s approach in other key growth markets outside of the US 
 Recruit, hire and develop diverse life cycle and early commercial teams; contribute and shape the companyâ€™s culture and values to drive impact for patients, customers and Caris 
 Proactively identify risk, inclusive of challenges/mitigation. 
 Provide commercial sign-off on all medically/clinically related content and messaging. 
 
 Requirements: 
 Knowledge, Skills, and Experience 
 Must have experience in commercial leadership, product strategy/marketing, life cycle management, preferably in Oncology 
 Prior healthcare leadership experience ( in vitro  diagnostic, medical device, pharmaceutical, etc.), molecular science experience preferred 
 Must be able to work across levels and functions (including, but not limited to Commercial teams, R&D, Medical Affairs, Market Access, Legal and Regulatory) in the organization to drive delivery of strategic decisions and priorities 
 Ability to develop, communicate and execute short and long-term strategic planning 
 Must be well organized and have the ability to meet strict deadlines and perform under pressure in a fast-paced work environment 
 Strong executive presence, presentation, communication and leadership skills 
 Proficient computer skills, which include Microsoft PowerPoint, Excel and Word 
 
 Education, Certification/Licensure, and/or Experience 
 PhD or MD degree required, MBA preferred
 15+ years product planning/marketing, lifecycle management and execution 
 Prior experience managing multi-level teams 
 
 Physical Demands
 The ability to lift objects over 30 pounds 
 The ability to sit or stand for long periods of time 
 Manual dexterity and ability to bend, reach, stoop 
 
